*περιπατέω / peripateō / per-ee-pat-eh'-o
=== Etymology ===

*From [[περί]] {{GG|4012}} and [[πατέω]] {{GG|3961}}; to tread all around, that is, walk at large (especially as proof of ability); figuratively to live, deport oneself, follow (as a companion or votary): 
=== Verb ===
go, be occupied with, [[walk]] (about).